## **Description**
The **Concatenate **operator allows to concatenate multiple input strings into a single string.

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

String

The first string that you want to concatenate

**inâ€¦**

String

The N-th string that you want to concatenate

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

String

The resulting string, obtained by concatenating the N input strings

## **![](data:image/png;base64,)****Settings**
- In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- Check the **Enable separator **checkbox to specify the character to use to separate the input strings to concatenate. Select the required character from the **Select separator **drop-down menu; the available options are:

**,**

- -

- **:**

- **|**

- **"**

- -

-  **_**

- **+**

- **#**

- *(empty space)*

> Tip

Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add item**) at the bottom of the drop-down menu to add a custom value to the list, then click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to confirm.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

> Tip

To rename an input node, click on its name to edit it.

To remove an input node from the list, move your mouse over it and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) 	in the **Action **column; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**NULL input (no input)**

The operator considers a NULL input as an empty string. The system logs a warning event.

**Input with NULL value**

The operator considers an input with NULL value as an empty string. The system logs a warning event.
